<br>
Stalking back towards her, I was still in half-transformation. The spear was strapped to my back, as my newly developed claws can tear through more than any sword. Just before my eyes transformed, as well, I shook away the inhibitions. No. Question the elf first. Then we hunt. Ok?<br>
<br>
..................................Fine.<br>
<br>
&quot;OPAL!&quot; I roared. I guess I still hadn't completely returned to human state, because he eyes went wide. I looked behind me to see a tail still snaking around. I grabbed her by her tunic, and pulled her close enough for her to see my fangs pulsing. &quot;What do you know. What did you tell her. What is going on. Speak before I get too hungry.&quot;<br>
<br>
!#$%^&amp;*!@#$%^&amp;*!@#$%^&amp;*<br>
<br>
The dead rats located that blasted mage for me again. Gods, I hate casters; too cocky, and they always run. Running after her with all the speed I could muster in human state, I finally got to her before she exited the gates. I grabbed on to her shoulder, and she spun around like a demon unleashed, and fire in her eyes. Guess she doesn't like being touched, eh?<br>
<br>
Damn! The fangs came back. Fur was still sprouting on my hands, somewhat. At least the feline eyes hadn't come yet...<br>
<br>
&quot;Business with *my* family is my business, as well, Paradise. That *is* your correct name, isn't it?&quot; I could tell she was going through her mind, listing the ways to torture Opal Darkbriar for speaking too much. That goes without saying. &quot;I know about the war. I know you need power. I suggest you enlist a seasoned general-   Myself. But, first,&quot; I grinned, showing the pearly whites, &quot;Please      apologize for destroying my last gift of love that remains.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uparadisetheheretic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Paradise the Heretic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mistress of Decay</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 1:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.globalrray.net/user/paradisetheheretic/paradise.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: the true paradises. . .</span><hr size=1> Paradise glarred at the man who had dared to touch her, unphased by his 'transformation'.  She spoke boldy and clearly, anunciating each sylabale to make sure she would nto have to repeat herself.<br>
