, he held open his eye and with the other, he squeezed a drop of blood from a small vial.  He repeated the procedure for the other eye, and then removed a glass jar of blue ink.  He had spent his last platinum piece on the vial, ink was a rare commodity, rarely wasted on cosmetical purposed.  He smeared the quick drying liquid over his face and hands.  Now for the final touch, he poured a mixture of ash and guanno in his water pouch.  He shook the liquid before carefully pouring it over his lustrious brown hair.  Brown faded into tan, and finally gray.  Were once had stood a handsome half elf, was a tall, blunt featured dark elf.  Praying to Prexus his disguise would work, he walked past the guards with an air of arrogance only a dark elf would have.  His disguise had worked..suprisingly.  Inside the entrance tunnels was a row of pikes upon which were the bodies of a group of halflings, most likely clerics.  A dark elf leaving the city glared at him as Matt shuddered.  He would have to hide not only his appearance, but his kind good nature as well, but he must find her.  If anything is true, I must find her, he thought. <p>Ignis Summa Pugnabat, The fires shall cleanse the world.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rillen>Rillen</A> at: 6/12/02 2:06:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umindles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kay Oss kNite</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 3:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Plays of Power</span><hr size=1> &quot;Backtalk to me, will you, bitch?&quot; I screamed. My tail snaked out fully, and I skipped the full animal stage of the Ner'Shalrok- the Blood Rage, the Lion Clan's special gift. I slashed across her belly, and my heightened hearing brought me to new levels of exhilliration as her screams pierced my very soul. The beauty turned suddenly ugly, enraged, and fearful for her life. Lightning was called down, and fire erupted upon my short fur. They struck me simultaneously, and a blizzard unlike anything the world had ever seen before blew in my face. I stepped through the mess of mana unscathed, just like with that blasted Rainkeeper. I grabbed her robes, and lifted her up with my left hand, just like that blasted Rainkeeper. Then, with feline eyes and a glorious golden mane, I devoured her entire head, JUST like that blasted Rainkeeper... Karana...<br>
<br>
I snapped out of my reverie. Standing before me was the beauty, looking into my eyes with deadly intent. She didn't know half of what she was getting in to... If only she'd traveled to the Plane of Storms lately... Yet again, like with everything on this damned plane of reality, I bit my tongue. Literally. Mustering all the self control I could, I snapped to attention, and curtly saluted her. A skeleton rounded the corner, carrying a few backpacks. &quot;I serve a higher purpose,&quot; I growled. I smoothed the anger out of my voice, and continued when I trusted my own vocal chords. &quot;But I am also a knight. I have my duties, and my loyalties,&quot; I grabbed the bags, and slung them over my shoulder, after removing a massive mace and hooking it onto my belt. &quot;I've led armies bigger than you've ever seen. I feel my presence would be helpful, if not necessary, in the coming battle.&quot;<br>
<br>
Her eyes seemed to grow in distaste. I could feel that she was about to say something else, possibley even strike me dad, so I acted. I walked past her, and out the gate, towards Neriak. I tossed a bag of provisions to her, and continued, &quot;Necessary, that is, if there's more in charge with sense like Opal Darkbriar.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubellonakali.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bellona Kali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Child of Hate</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 5:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pmp.4t.com/magelo/smallbell.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lightwalkers do not belong in the shadows</span><hr size=1> Bellona could feel him. Light skined turned another color is still light in the end. Spinning around, she see's a darkelf. He seems lost in Neriak, completely unsure of which way to turn. His movements are graceful, more so than that of a Teir'Dal, even though he appears as one. Bellona takes notice of how he avoids the guards... In seconds she is upon him, her nails ripping through the neckline of his tunic and pressing him up against a wall. Her voice hisses.<br>
