<br>
I walked along the trodden paths in the Commonlands for a little bit. I looked to the sky, and the clouds, and to the green grass and healthy trees. I never really knew how much I missed this, I guess; that blasted Curse kept me from seeing anything clearly, except for my family...<br>
<br>
I made it to the Nektulos forest by dark. I loved that place at midnight; it felt like home. I passed a massive stone golem, and he saluted as I walked past. I saluted back with a smirk, and continued my walk through the forest, my Deadeye spell working beautifully to cut through the black. I had a pet skeleton reanimated to carry my gear for most of the way; after all, I was walking in my flayed skin and magical leathers. Ain't no WAY I'm trekking again with all that platemail. As a result, I tend to set a faster pace than most fighters. Only problem was that my pet crumbled soon enough, and I turned just in time to see the flash of steel cut through the spine of Kobn. DAMN! I lose more pets that way...<br>
<br>
I scooped out a crustacean shell breastplate and fitted it over the flayed skin tunic quickly, while drawing my shadowed mace and shield of trapped souls. I brought my sheild up in a defensive position just fast enough to block a shadowy arrow. It disentigrated as soon as it touched the plate. Dust fell to the ground, and snakes started to writhe up out of the dirt. &quot;No... Not here! Not like this! NOT HERE!&quot; I scooped up my gear, and ran like the nine hells were pursuing me, because, in all reality...<br>
