 Neriak without fear encompassing their entire being?  From within the burlap sack, he removed a green necklace.  He slowly slipped it over his neck.  The cool material felt refreshing against his skin.  Matteus looked down at his blue arms, shaking his head.  Without a thought, he dove into the murky waters below leaving behind a stream of blue and white in the water as his guise slipped off his skin.  For a minute, his fears and thoughts were left behind in the world of hate, her world. <p>Ignis Summa Pugnabat, The fires shall cleanse the world.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/usuedydar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Suedydar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/02 11:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Silent are watching...</span><hr size=1>   He ran through the streets of Felwithe, into the Paladin's guild, and into a secret passageway; known to only a few in Felwithe. He opens a door and salutes the man inside. &quot;General Suedydar, sir. We have received word from the Silent Watchers stationed in Freeport that there in tension brewing. Apparenty, the Necromancers are on the brink of war on the Paladins, possibly with aid coming from Qeynos and Neriak.&quot; He hands a scroll to the General. Suedydar reads the scroll, his eyes widening as he finishes reading. &quot;This could be trouble if the Necromancers are involved. It won't be a war, it will be a blood-bath. Send word back to the Watchers to keep me informed on this matter. Also, inform King Tearis Thex. This is to remain Top Secret.&quot; Handing the scroll back to the Private, he sits down at his desk. &quot;What am I going to do..what am I going t