e odd noises were.  Shouting and cheers were coming from within the city.  His curiosity yet again got the better of his as he removed a tiny flute from his pocket.  He raised the wood to his lips and emmitted a long low note.  White mist flowed forth from the end.  Mist clung to his skin, hiding him behind its obscurity.  As the mist faded, so did all remnants of Matt.  He continued to quietly play the song as he crept into the city.  Beyond the first gate, hundreds of Tier'dal stood together.  From they shouting and cheers he made out four words, &quot;Hate, War, Kill, and Paineel.&quot;  It didn't take an erudite to figure out what those four added up to.  The site of a sea of tier'dal was enough to frighten even Matt.  With haste, he fled the city of hate.  They shall wage war, but what is to happen in Paineel?  Shall they make their stand their..if so, who is attacking.?  I must get to Paineel, soon. <p>Ignis Summa Pugnabat, The fires shall cleanse the world.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/bfantasystoriesforum.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rillen>Rillen</A> at: 6/14/02 6:01:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umindles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kay Oss kNite</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/15/02 8:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Battered</span><hr size=1> I dislodged the mace from another skull quickly, and brought my sheild up to blow another folly of arrows. My reserves of power had been depleated by summoning the undead beasts to aid me; how foolish it was, too, as they'd all been cut down within minutes. I sucked the life force and flesh from another dozen, but they came anyways. I was nearly exhausted, but I'd yet to see one Slayer, and we all know what that means...<br>
<br>
Trouble.<br>
<br>
The magic on the green, scaled armor of the Clan of the Snake was enough to make even the greatest oak decay in minutes, if focused correctly. The stench of disease and the aroma of death meant nothing to me; the taint of the Snakes did. Swinging the mace again to try and remove some of the brain and skullbone that had come along with it, I tripped over a root. Another elf in green swung a longsword at me, and I parried just in time. My foot came up, and I flung him ten feet away. I was up on my feet and running again, and I was nearly to Neriak! YES! With that deadly woman and Bell, we had more than enough to push these foot soldiers back through the gate, and these plane-jumping fools wouldn't plague Norrath again... Well, until they found another gate, but still...<br>
<br>
The fact that they'd even FOUND us here was amazing; I've been jumping planes for aeons now, and they've never tracked me, once. Odd. I didn't have time to ponder, however, before I was clubbed from behind. I rolled forward, dropped my bags of armor, and grabbed a scimitar, gripping it in my other hand, hoping I could duel wield for a bit. Looking up, I knew I needed it.<br>
<br>
He was big like a barbarian. He had a long, black cloak of living shadow. He carried only one Death-tainted longsword, and his green platemail gave of the stench of Kai all around. &quot;Go back to your false god, freak!&quot; I spat. &quot;Kai is *NOTHING* on this plane; The Lions will defeat you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The Balance will be tipped, you furry freak,&quot; his voice sounded like steel grating across granite, and the dark green helm, the head of a snake with its fangs dropping on either side of his face, glistened in the darkness. &quot;Death will be all. Kai will reward us. Stand down.&quot; He rose his sword, and brought it down, slicing through my poor travelling armor, and slicing into my left arm. I shouted, and crushed his breastplate with my mace.<br>
<br>
My left arm came back up, and chopped down at his neck. He parried, and I crushed him in the head, knocking off the helm. He kicked my in the stomach, and I rolled backwards, grabbed my bags, and made a mad dash for Neriak, all the while screaming, &quot;Our forces are great! We will CRUSH you! The Lions live AGAAAIN!&quot;<br>
<br>
I finally made it to the entrance, but there were no guards! WHY were there no guards?? This was getting harder and harder...<br>
<br>
The Slayer dove and caught my foot. His forked tongue flicked out, and his eyes went serpentine on me- he was about to bite. I crushed him in the head, and slashed at his face, but he knocked the scimitar out of my hand easily. He clawed his way up my body, his weight nearly crushing me, and I felt the rage risin in my again; my fangs elongated, and I dropped the mace, slashing him across the face.<br>
<br>
A few minutes of bloody struggle went by, rolling, hitting, scraping, and vying for the neck bite; a quick finish. I finally got on top of him, and planted my knee in his chest, underneath the breastplate. I rolled, and kicked up with the other knee, sending him tumbling out into the forest. I grabbed my weapons, and my battered and beaten form ran into the cave just as the first ranks of Tier'Dal started marching. I backed up, confused, and turned to the Slayer. He was still standing there, looking more like a serpent. I was well recognized in Neriak, and was allowed to move aside or being sliced to ribbons. I chose the first. I looked back as the columns started moving out; the Slayer was gone. I couldn't smell the vile taint of Kai anywhere. I guess they fled, the first intelligent thing I've seen a Snake do in centuries.<br>
<br>
&quot;I gotta tell Bellona... I never explained the Balance to her fully, but she's gotta believe me in this,&quot; I turned, and waited for the wave of black skinned elves to file out, scanning for Bellona all the while. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showMessageRange?topicID=2.topic&start=181&stop=184>10</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showPrevMessage?topicID=2.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showNextMessage?topicID=2.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=40><img src=http://Auction.2y.net/user/paradisetheheretic/addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pu